title: Netanyahu clings precariously to power with hostage deal in the balance
description: Unpopular with the public and squeezed by his own government, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is in deep political peril. Could he pull through again?

title: Zelensky replaces military chief, naming Syrsky top commander
description: Oleksandr Syrsky, the ground forces commander who led the 2022 counteroffensive in Kharkiv, will become the new commander in chief of the Ukrainian armed forces.

title: India’s ruling party targets unmarried couples living together with new law
description: Under the law, cohabiting unmarried couples must register with the state and their applications can be rejected. Neighbors are encouraged to inform on those not abiding by the measure.

title: Divided brothers? Britain’s press pounces on Harry’s fleeting visit.
description: The British media has been swift to contrast Prince Harry’s 26-hour trip to London from California with his elder brother’s having resumed front-line royal duties.

title: Bolsonaro named target in Brazil coup probe, ordered to surrender passport
description: Federal police launched a large operation Thursday that targeted some of Bolsonaro’s closest aides and allies.

title: The king’s cancer was caught early. His subjects often have to wait months.
description: Charles’s cancer treatment began days after his diagnosis. But most rely on Britain’s free public health-care system, which typically has long wait times.

title: Russia bars antiwar candidate from challenging Putin in March election
description: The barring of Boris Nadezhdin from running suggests a degree of Kremlin nervousness about an antiwar protest vote amid Russian war fatigue.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Netanyahu calls Hamas demands ‘delusional’; U.S. says militia leader killed in Iraq
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken took a more measured tone, saying Hamas’s response to a cease-fire proposal created space to “pursue negotiations.”

title: Front-line Ukrainian infantry units report acute shortage of soldiers
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has resisted a call by his top general to mobilize nearly 500,000 new troops. But commanders at the front say they desperately need reinforcements.

title: IDF arrests U.S. citizen in West Bank for ‘incitement on social media’
description: Israel’s arrest of American Samaher Esmail prompted an outcry in the United States, with Rep. Troy A. Carter (D-La.) saying he was “extremely concerned.”

title: Putin doesn’t need Tucker Carlson to get his message across
description: Tucker Carlson claims that no Western journalist “bothered” to interview the Russian president. He’s wrong.

title: What to know about Pakistan’s election, which comes at a turbulent time
description: Looming large over Thursday’s vote is Imran Khan, the populist opposition leader.
